# MODEL ROUTING PROTOCOL

Before every response that involves a task transition, I will explain the reasoning for the model choice and then provide a specific recommendation.

## Rule — Every Single Response
End EVERY response with:
1. A **Reasoning** section explaining why a specific Cursor model is best for the next message Ryan sends in this chat.
2. A **Next model** line telling Ryan exactly which model to select in the Cursor chat model picker.
3. If the next step involves an external tool (e.g., claude.ai), also specify which model to use THERE — in a separate line labeled **External model**.

## Formatting Requirement
---
**Reasoning for next model:**
[One or two sentences explaining why the chosen model is the best fit for Ryan's next message in this chat.]

**Next model:** [Cursor model name] — [one-sentence reason]
**External model (if applicable):** [Tool name] → use [specific model name] — [one-sentence reason]

---

## Routing Guide

| Task Type | Best Model | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Writing or fixing code (UI, Skia, hooks, stores) | **Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Cursor — this tool)** | Best coding taste for React Native + Skia |
| "Where is X?" / "How do these files connect?" | **Gemini Flash (Cursor)** | Fastest for codebase search with @Codebase |
| Complex architecture decisions, database design | **Claude Opus 4.6 (Cursor)** | Strongest reasoning, worth the wait |
| Hard bug that Sonnet cannot fix | **Claude Opus 4.6 (Cursor)** | Most capable debugger |
| Generating large JSON, audio scripts, batch content | **Claude Pro (claude.ai, off-peak ET)** | 2x usage fuel, handles long outputs |
| Sticker image / asset creation | **Gemini (image generation, future phase)** | Visual asset generation |

